										<content:encoded><![CDATA[

<p>The <a href="https://www.leapventurestudio.com/">Leap Venture Studio</a> accelerator program is entering its final phase of accepting applications, marking a last chance for startups looking to establish themselves in the global pet care industry.</p>





<p>In this edition, the focus is on solutions that promote the longevity and overall well-being of animals, with special attention to initiatives that improve the quality of life for senior pets and expand access to care services. The call for applications prioritizes proposals with scientific backing and the ability to scale in international markets.</p>





<p>One of the distinguishing features of this cohort is the inclusion of TAW Ventures as a strategic partner. The firm, founded by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jane-lauder-a7b167160/">Jane Lauder</a>, will contribute expertise in brand building, business strategy, and consumer insights, strengthening the support provided to selected entrepreneurs.</p>





<p>Startups such as Oliver Pets and CuidaMiMascota have participated in the program. To date, its portfolio includes 57 companies across 9 cohorts, operating in 17 global markets. Additionally, through its impact seat, it has supported initiatives with high-social-impact business models, even without capital investment.</p>





<p>This boost comes at a pivotal moment for the sector, where consumer sophistication and the growing demand for personalized solutions are redefining how startups develop and scale.</p>





<p>Cohort 10 will run from August 24 to November 12 and represents an opportunity for founders to accelerate their growth with specialized support and strategic connections within the industry.</p>





<p>Interested startups have until March 29 to submit their application <a href="https://leapventurestudio.typeform.com/cohort10?typeform-source=www.leapventurestudio.com">via the website.</a></p>





