					<description><![CDATA[ADvendio announced the launch of the Revenue OS for Agentic Advertising, a new category of technology designed to reclaim the 28% of the workday currently lost to manual human middleware tasks. At the heart of this shift is AdOne (formerly ADvendio One), the core engine built to plan, execute, and solve problems autonomously with enterprise-grade [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>ADvendio announced the launch of the Revenue OS for Agentic Advertising, a new category of technology designed to reclaim the 28% of the workday currently lost to manual human middleware tasks. At the heart of this shift is AdOne (formerly ADvendio One), the core engine built to plan, execute, and solve problems autonomously with enterprise-grade precision.</p>



<p>For organizations seeking targeted transformation, <a href="https://www.advendio.com/">ADvendio</a> also introduces three specialized agentic standalone solutions—AdGateway, AdFinance, and AdPortal—each powered by a dedicated workforce of agents to handle the industry’s most arduous manual processes.</p>



<p>The global advertising industry has crossed the $1 trillion spend threshold, yet it remains tethered to a silent efficiency gap. For a decade, the market has relied on software that waits—tools that move data but require constant human intervention to manage complexity.</p>



<p>&#8220;The market is at a tipping point,&#8221; says Julian Ahrends, CTO at ADvendio. &#8220;The shift from chatbots to autonomous agents is exciting, but speed is a liability without guardrails. Most AI isn&#8217;t built to understand the consequences of a bad trade or a compliance error. We’ve spent years building the operational logic—things like margin protection and global tax rules—directly into the platform. This ensures that when an agent acts, it’s not just following a prompt; it’s following the hard business rules that actually protect a company&#8217;s bottom line.&#8221;</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-agentic-standalone-solutions-and-their-specialized-agents">Agentic Standalone Solutions and Their Specialized Agents</h2>



<p>The Revenue OS empowers media teams through specialized agentic workforces within three standalone solutions that fit easily into your existing systems:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>AdGateway</strong>: Unify your data, agents, integrations, and channels to streamline your operations into a single, intelligent sales flow for effortless scalability. AdGateway comes with our inventory, optimization, and targeting agents to boost efficiency and drive cross-departmental optimizations.</li>



<li><strong>AdFinance</strong>: Turn finance into a secure, streamlined, agile operation with AdFinance and its Salesforce-native AI agents, including our invoicing and month-end agents to accelerate time to revenue and closing timelines in a secure, audit-proof way.</li>



<li><strong>AdPortal</strong>: Add an autonomous self-service ad sales solution to your stack and watch your sales capacity multiply with AdPortal’s seller, sales enablement, and proposal agents while always providing you with full oversight and control.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-built-on-authority-not-hype">Built on Authority, Not Hype</h2>



<p>While the market is flooded with thin AI wrappers, ADvendio’s Revenue OS is anchored in the secure Salesforce ecosystem. It harnesses intelligence exactly where the data lives, ensuring that every autonomous action is governed by deep operational logic—including tax, billing, and compliance—required for global scale.</p>



<p>ADvendio will make the Revenue OS for Agentic Advertising available to global markets in Q1 2026, offering a clear path for media companies to move from managing chaos to capturing autonomous revenue.</p>
